{
  "title": "Odoo \u2014 Per Namespace: CPU / RAM / Overlay / PVC / Workers",
  "uid": "odoo-ns-deep-dive",
  "schemaVersion": 37,
  "version": 1,
  "refresh": "30s",
  "time": {
    "from": "now-3h",
    "to": "now"
  },
  "panels": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "type": "text",
      "title": "\u2139\ufe0f Zero-change monitoring \u2014 how it works",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 3,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 0
      },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "All metrics come from **cAdvisor** (built into kubelet) and **kube-state-metrics** \u2014 both already running. No changes to Odoo pods, no addons, no sidecars.\n\n**Overlay** = the container writable layer (files written inside the container above the image). Grows when Odoo writes logs, temp files, or any path not on a mounted volume. High overlay = files escaping your PVCs \u2192 will fill the node's container runtime disk.\n\n> Worker counts use the process-exporter DaemonSet (already deployed). Because multiple namespaces share nodes, worker counts show the node total \u2014 divide by number of Odoo instances on that node for per-namespace estimate."
      },
      "datasource": null
    },
    {
      "id": 10,
      "type": "row",
      "title": "\ud83d\udcca Live Snapshot \u2014 Per Namespace",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 1,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 3
      },
      "collapsed": false
    },
    {
      "id": 11,
      "type": "stat",
      "title": "CPU Cores Used",
      "description": "Total CPU cores consumed across all Odoo containers in selected namespaces.",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 4,
        "w": 4,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 4
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "sum(rate(container_cpu_usage_seconds_total{namespace=~\"$namespace\",container=~\"$container\",container!=\"\",container!=\"POD\"}[$__rate_interval]))",
          "refId": "A",
          "legendFormat": ""
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "short",
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {
                "color": "green",
                "value": null
              },
              {
                "color": "yellow",
                "value": 2
              },
              {
                "color": "red",
                "value": 4
              }
            ]
          }
        }
      },
      "options": {
        "reduceOptions": {
          "calcs": [
            "lastNotNull"
          ]
        },
        "colorMode": "background",
        "graphMode": "area"
      },
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 12,
      "type": "stat",
      "title": "CPU Throttling",
      "description": "% of CPU scheduling periods throttled. >20% = CPU limit is too tight \u2192 slow responses even at low CPU%.",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 4,
        "w": 4,
        "x": 4,
        "y": 4
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "avg(rate(container_cpu_cfs_throttled_periods_total{namespace=~\"$namespace\",container=~\"$container\",container!=\"\",container!=\"POD\"}[$__rate_interval]) / clamp_min(rate(container_cpu_cfs_periods_total{namespace=~\"$namespace\",container=~\"$container\",container!=\"\",container!=\"POD\"}[$__rate_interval]),0.001))",
          "refId": "A",
          "legendFormat": ""
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "percentunit",
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {
                "color": "green",
                "value": null
              },
              {
                "color": "yellow",
                "value": 0.2
              },
              {
                "color": "red",
                "value": 0.4
              }
            ]
          }
        }
      },
      "options": {
        "reduceOptions": {
          "calcs": [
            "lastNotNull"
          ]
        },
        "colorMode": "background",
        "graphMode": "area"
      },
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus"
      }
    },
